switchBasicEntry.name: switchBasicEntry
switchBasicEntry.description: Identification information about a particular port on the switch.

switchProductCode.name: switchProductCode
switchProductCode.description: An ASCII string giving the product code of the switch.

switchSerialNumber.name: switchSerialNumber
switchSerialNumber.description: An ASCII string giving the switch serial number.

switchPlaceOfManufacture.name: switchPlaceOfManufacture
switchPlaceOfManufacture.description: A number identifying where the switch was built.

switchDateOfManufacture.name: switchDateOfManufacture
switchDateOfManufacture.description: An ASCII string giving the date of manufacture of the switch.

switchMacAddress.name: switchMacAddress
switchMacAddress.description: The IEEE 802 MAC address of the switch.

switchCodeVersion.name: switchCodeVersion
switchCodeVersion.description: An ASCII string giving the version number of the switch software.

switchBpeEnabled.name: switchBpeEnabled
switchBpeEnabled.description: Setting this variable to TRUE (1) causes the bridge protocol engine to perform the Spanning Tree Protocol as defined in IEEE802.1d. Setting this variable to FALSE (0) causes the BPE to stop performing the Spanning Tree Protocol. The value of this variable when the switch starts operating is 1.

eraseSwitchSnmpConfigInfo.name: eraseSwitchSnmpConfigInfo
eraseSwitchSnmpConfigInfo.description: Setting this variable to TRUE (1) causes the switch to erase its SNMP configuration information both from memory and from permanent store. The switch the requests new configuration information using the BOOTP protocol. Setting this variable to any other value has no effect. This variable will always return 0 when read.

restoreSwitchDot1dDefaults.name: restoreSwitchDot1dDefaults
restoreSwitchDot1dDefaults.description: Setting this variable to TRUE (1) causes the BPE to restore the default spanning tree values given in the IEEE 802.1d specification. This resets all writeable Bridge MIB variables in the dot1dStp group of the Bridge MIB. Setting the variable to any other value has no effect. This variable will always return 0 when read.

performSwitchReset.name: performSwitchReset
performSwitchReset.description: Setting this variable to TRUE (1) causes the switch to perform a cold restart. As a result of this action a coldRestart trap will be sent. Setting this variable to any other value has no effect. This variable will always return 0 when read.

switchIdentPressed.name: switchIdentPressed
switchIdentPressed.description: This variable is TRUE (1) if the IDENTIFY button on the switch has been pressed since the variable was last read. After this variable has been read it will be set to 0.

ageFilterDatabase.name: ageFilterDatabase
ageFilterDatabase.description: Setting this variable to FALSE (0) causes the switch to stop aging out entries from its filter database. Setting this variable to TRUE (1) causes the switch to age out filter database entries as defined in IEEE 802.1D. This variable is set to 0 whenever the Switch restarts.

clearStatistics.name: clearStatistics
clearStatistics.description: Setting this variable to TRUE (1) clears the traffic statistics accumulators in the switch. Setting this variable to any other value has no effect. The variable always returns 0 when read.

switchBasicIndex.name: switchBasicIndex
switchBasicIndex.description: This is a dummy variable which provides a meta-index for the Basic Information Table.

switchPortTable.name: switchPortTable
switchPortTable.description: Identification information about the ports on a switch.

switchPortEntry.name: switchPortEntry
switchPortEntry.description: Identification information about a particular port on the switch.

switchPortIndex.name: switchPortIndex
switchPortIndex.description: The number of the port to which the management information applies.

switchPortProductCode.name: switchPortProductCode
switchPortProductCode.description: An ASCII string giving the product code of the card on which this port is located.

switchPortSerialNumber.name: switchPortSerialNumber
switchPortSerialNumber.description: An ASCII string giving the serial number of the card on which this port is located.

switchPortPlaceOfManufacture.name: switchPortPlaceOfManufacture
switchPortPlaceOfManufacture.description: A number identifying where the card on which this port is located was built.

switchPortDateOfManufacture.name: switchPortDateOfManufacture
switchPortDateOfManufacture.description: An ASCII string giving the date of manufacture of the card on which this port is located.

switchPortState.name: switchPortState
switchPortState.description: An ASCII string giving the port's operational state.

switchPortHighSensitivity.name: switchPortHighSensitivity
switchPortHighSensitivity.description: This variable is only valid if the port is an Ethernet port. If this variable is set to TRUE (1), the receiver of the Ethernet NIC controlling the port is set to high sensitivity. If the variable is set to 0, the port is set to normal sensitivity. If the ports on both ends of the 10BaseT link are set to high sensitivity, the maximum permissable length of the link is increased from 100 meters to 120 meters. Caution: a high sensitivity receiver may be overdriven by transmitters closer than 100 meters. This variable is 0 when the switch is powered up for the first time. Changes to this variable are preserved across system restarts.

restoreFddiMibDefaults.name: restoreFddiMibDefaults
restoreFddiMibDefaults.description: This variable is ony valid if the port is an FDDI station. Setting this variable to TRUE (1) causes the agent to restore the default MIB values given in the ANSI X3T9.5/84-49 Rev 7.2 specification. This resets all writable FDDI MIB variables. Setting the variable to any other value has no effect. This variable will always return 0 when read.

translateAllEthertypes.name: translateAllEthertypes
translateAllEthertypes.description: This variable is only valid if the port is an FDDI port. If this variable is set to TRUE (1), the Bridge Tunnel Encapsulation Protocol will be applied to frames containing any Ethertypes, not just the ones in the Selective Translation Table. If this variable is set to FALSE (0), the protocol will only be applied to Ethertypes in the translation table.

switchPortTxFrames.name: switchPortTxFrames
switchPortTxFrames.description: This counter is incremented by one for each frame transmitted to the network segment attached to the port.

switchPortRxFrames.name: switchPortRxFrames
switchPortRxFrames.description: This counter is incremented by one for each valid frame received from the network segment attached to the port.

switchPortFcsErrors.name: switchPortFcsErrors
switchPortFcsErrors.description: This counter is incremented by one for each received frame which failed its FCS check.

switchPortFilterDiscards.name: switchPortFilterDiscards
switchPortFilterDiscards.description: The number of frames received on this port which have been discarded due to the filtering action of the port's bridge circuit.

switchPortDelayExceededDiscards.name: switchPortDelayExceededDiscards
switchPortDelayExceededDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to excessive transit delay through the switch. It reports the same value as the object dot1dBasePortDelayExceededDiscards in the Bridge MIB (RFC 1493).

switchPortMtuExceededDiscards.name: switchPortMtuExceededDiscards
switchPortMtuExceededDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to excessive size. It is the same value reported in the object dot1dBasePortMtuExceededDiscards in the Bridge MIB (RFC 1493).

switchSelectiveTranslationTable.name: switchSelectiveTranslationTable
switchSelectiveTranslationTable.description: The Selective Translation Table as defined in IEEE 802.1h.

translationTablePortIndex.name: translationTablePortIndex
translationTablePortIndex.description: The table index - the port number on which the STT resides.

translationTableEthertype1.name: translationTableEthertype1
translationTableEthertype1.description: The first Ethertype for which the Bridge Tunnel Encapsulation Protocol should be used.

translationTableEntryValid1.name: translationTableEntryValid1
translationTableEntryValid1.description: If this variable is set to TRUE (1), the Bridge Tunnel Encapsulation Protocol will be applied to frames containing the first Ethertype. If this variable is set to FALSE (0), the protocol will not be applied to the Ethertype.

translationTableEthertype2.name: translationTableEthertype2
translationTableEthertype2.description: The second Ethertype for which the Bridge Tunnel Encapsulation Protocol should be used.

translationTableEntryValid2.name: translationTableEntryValid2
translationTableEntryValid2.description: If this variable is set to TRUE (1), the Bridge Tunnel Encapsulation Protocol will be applied to frames containing the second Ethertype. If this variable is set to FALSE (0), the protocol will not be applied to the Ethertype.

translationTableEthertype3.name: translationTableEthertype3
translationTableEthertype3.description: The third Ethertype for which the Bridge Tunnel Encapsulation Protocol should be used.

translationTableEntryValid3.name: translationTableEntryValid3
translationTableEntryValid3.description: If this variable is set to TRUE (1), the Bridge Tunnel Encapsulation Protocol will be applied to frames containing the third Ethertype. If this variable is set to FALSE (0), the protocol will not be applied to the Ethertype.

switchTouched.name: switchTouched
switchTouched.description: This trap is generated when the IDENTIFY button on the switch is pressed. The agent throttles the generation of consecutive switchTouched traps so that there is at least a two second gap between them.
